# escritha-api вЂ” Code Standards (NestJS + Prisma + PostgreSQL)

## Folder structure

```
src/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ core/               # Cross-cutting concerns: guards, decorators, filters, global interceptors
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ decorators/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ filters/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ guards/
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ interceptors/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ shared/             # Resources shared across modules
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ constants/      # APP_CONSTANTS and similar
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ dto/            # Generic DTOs (PaginationDto, BaseResponseDto)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ enums/          # Global enums
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ interfaces/     # ApiResponse, ErrorResponse, PaginatedResponse
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ prisma/         # PrismaService
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ types/          # Auxiliary types (e.g. request-with-user.type)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ utils/          # Global utility functions
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ features/           # Large, composed feature sets
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ edition/        # e.g. compilation, conversion, section, pdf, footnote
в””в”Ђв”Ђ <domain>/           # Each domain has its own folder
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ dto/
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ <domain>.module.ts
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ <domain>.controller.ts
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ <domain>.service.ts
```

### Where to put things
- Logic reused across multiple modules в†’ `src/shared/utils/`
- Guard/interceptor/filter applied globally в†’ `src/core/`
- DTO used by only one module в†’ `src/<domain>/dto/`
- DTO used by multiple modules в†’ `src/shared/dto/`
- Large feature with several sub-responsibilities в†’ `src/features/<name>/`

---

## Global naming conventions

- **Folders and files**: `kebab-case`
- **Classes and interfaces**: `PascalCase`
- **Functions and variables**: `camelCase`
- **Global constants**: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- **Never** use obscure abbreviations вЂ” prefer full, descriptive names
- Code, comments, and file names: **English**
- Error messages shown to end users: **Portuguese (pt-BR)**

---

## Known inconsistencies вЂ” never replicate these

1. Do **not** use `@UseGuards(AuthGuard('jwt'))` manually вЂ” `JwtAuthGuard` is already global via `CoreModule`
2. Do **not** mix `AuthGuard('jwt')` with `JwtAuthGuard` in the same controller
3. Prisma fields must use `snake_case` in the schema with `@map()` for TypeScript camelCase compatibility

---

## Creating a new domain module

Required structure:

```
src/<kebab-case-name>/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ dto/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ create-<name>.dto.ts
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ update-<name>.dto.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ <name>.module.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ <name>.controller.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ <name>.service.ts
в””в”Ђв”Ђ index.ts            в†ђ barrel export
```

`index.ts` must re-export everything:
```ts
export * from './<name>.module';
export * from './<name>.service';
export * from './<name>.controller';
```

Register the module in `src/app.module.ts` under the correct section (feature, admin, or cross-cutting).

